Title: Customization: Ideal Varieties, Product Uniqueness and Price Competition
Abstract: We study customization in the Hotelling model with two firms. In addition to providing ideal 
varieties, the perceived uniqueness of a customized product contributes independently to consumer utility. We 
show that only when consumer preferences for uniqueness are high customization occurs in equilibrium.
